<TITLE> New allowance structure proposed for SC judges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jul 6 (bdnews24.com)A parliamentary watchdog has backed an amendment to a law proposing a new dearness and recreation allowances for Supreme Court judges. Suranjit Sengupta, president of the parliamentary standing committee on law, placed a report supporting the amendment to the Supreme Court Judges (Remuneration and Privileges) Act 1978 in parliament on Monday. Speaker Abdul Hamid had sent the bill for the proposed amendment to the standing committee on March 2. The committee has recommended dearness allowance for Supreme Court judges at a rate of 20 percent of salary and a recreation allowance to be paid every three years, similar to that of civil servants. bdnews2
